ydrogen peroxide production","Blocks iodine organification"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ETSH acts on thyroid follicular cells through G-protein coupled receptors, increasing intracellular cyclic adenosine monophosphate (cAMP). This leads to multiple effects:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased sodium-iodide symporter expression\u003C/strong\u003E in the basolateral membrane, enhancing iodine uptake\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased thyroglobulin synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - TSH actually increases thyroglobulin production\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReduced follicular cell size\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - TSH promotes hypertrophy and hyperplasia\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInhibited hydrogen peroxide production\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - TSH increases hydrogen peroxide production needed for iodination\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EBlocked iodine organification\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect - TSH enhances the incorporation of iodine into thyroglobulin\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH) has multiple effects on thyroid follicular cells including increasing iodine uptake, thyroglobulin synthesis, and promoting cell growth","TSH acts through G-protein coupled receptors to increase cyclic adenosine monophosphate (cAMP) in thyroid follicular cells"],"references":["Brent GA. Mechanisms of thyroid hormone action. J Clin Invest. 2012 Sep;122(9):3035-43. doi: 10.1172/JCI60047. Epub 2012 Sep 4. PMID: 22945636; PMCID: PMC3433956","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (201